results.name: Number of times the digit 0 appears in the decimal expansion of n^3.
comment: The cubes corresponding to the first occurrence of 1, 2, 3, ... are listed in A036527, i.e., A048365(n) = A036527(n)^(1/3) is the index of the first occurrence of n.
link: Robert Israel, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000
xref: Analog for squares: A086008 (digit 0), and A086009 - A086017 for digits 1 - 9.
